---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="About Ilyas Alhassan — Data Scientist and AI Engineer." />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main id="main-content">
			<article>
				<p class="eyebrow">About</p>
				<h1>Ilyas Alhassan</h1>

				<p class="lede">
					I ship AI systems for a living. I write about the gap between
					the demo and the deploy.
				</p>

				<h2>What I work on</h2>
				<p>
					I'm a Data Scientist and AI Engineer at Bio-Techne, where I lead
					GenAI initiatives across the company. I've shipped a multi-agent
					sales intelligence platform serving hundreds of weekly users, a
					production technical-support assistant retrieving over a million
					Salesforce records, document intelligence pipelines that process
					PDFs at scale, and decision agents that have to answer correctly
					the first time because there isn't a second chance.
				</p>
				<p>
					Before GenAI was a category, I built classical machine learning
					systems — recommendation engines, predictive pipelines, anomaly
					detection — and ML pipelines for protein engineering that
					commercialized AI-designed therapeutics. The tools change every
					six months. The hard parts don't.
				</p>

				<h2>What I write about</h2>
				<p>
					Most public writing about AI right now is either hype or theory.
					There's a shortage of writing from the people actually shipping
					these systems into regulated, high-stakes environments where
					"the model hallucinated" is an incident, not a tweet.
				</p>
				<p>
					This site is my contribution to closing that gap. Specifics over
					generalities. Scars over claims. The things I wish someone had
					written before I had to figure them out the hard way.
				</p>
				<p>
					Topics I keep returning to: grounded retrieval, evaluation that
					survives reality, agent architecture, production failure modes,
					and the long unglamorous middle between a demo and a system you
					can run at three in the morning when something breaks.
				</p>

				<h2>Get in touch</h2>
				<div class="contact">
					<div class="contact-row">
						<span class="contact-label">Email</span>
						<a href="mailto:hello@ilyashassan.dev">hello@ilyashassan.dev</a>
					</div>
					<div class="contact-row">
						<span class="contact-label">LinkedIn</span>
						<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ilyasalhassan/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">/in/ilyasalhassan</a>
					</div>
					<div class="contact-row">
						<span class="contact-label">GitHub</span>
						<a href="https://github.com/ilyas-hassan" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@ilyas-hassan</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</article>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.eyebrow {
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		color: var(--muted);
		letter-spacing: 0.02em;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
	}

	article h1 {
		font-size: 2.75rem;
		line-height: 1.05;
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
	}

	.lede {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		line-height: 1.55;
		color: var(--muted);
		max-width: 52ch;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
	}

	article h2 {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		color: var(--muted);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		margin-top: var(--space-6);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
		padding-bottom: var(--space-2);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
	}

	article p {
		font-size: 1.0625rem;
		line-height: 1.75;
		color: var(--ink);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
	}

	.contact {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.5rem;
		margin-top: var(--space-2);
	}

	.contact-row {
		display: flex;
		gap: 1.5rem;
		align-items: baseline;
		font-size: 1.0625rem;
	}

	.contact-label {
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		color: var(--muted);
		min-width: 5rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		article h1 {
			font-size: 2.25rem;
		}

		.lede {
			font-size: 1.1rem;
		}

		.contact-row {
			gap: 0.75rem;
		}

		.contact-label {
			min-width: 4rem;
			font-size: 0.8rem;
		}
	}
</style>